7.
    a.
        Because it binds irreversibly and preferentially to haemoglobin, causing not enough oxygen to be carried to our cells, causing asphyxiation.
    b.
        There is no effect when a nickel catalyst is used as a catalyst simply increases the speed at which equilibrium is reached, but has no effect on the position of the equilibrium itself; consequently, no more or less hydrogen is produced.
    c.
        i.
            Temperature is lowered. There is no change in pressure. The position of equilibrium moves to resist this change in temperature. Since the rightwards reaction is endothermic, and the leftwards exothermic, the position of equilibrium must move left; hence, less hydrogen is produced, so the yield is lower.
        ii.
            Temperature is not changed. But, pressure is lowered. There are more moles of substances on the right of the reaction (3 + 1 = 4) than on the left ( 1 + 1 = 2; 4 > 2). So, the position of equilibrium moves to counteract the decrease in temperature: i.e. it moves right. So, more hydrogen is produced, so the yield is higher.
